ions[2].keyword) Step 6: Check Observation - Found keyword [request, response] in Metric data (From GT key_observations[3].keyword) Step 7: Check Observation - Found keyword [pod_memory_working_set_bytes] in Metric data (From GT key_observations[4].keyword) Step 8: Check Observation - Found keyword [pod_network_receive_bytes, pod_network_receive_packets, pod_network_transmit_bytes, pod_network_transmit_packets] in Metric data (From GT key_observations[5].keyword) Step 9: Derive Root Cause - Based on above features, determined cause is [rrt, rrt_max, request, response, pod_network_receive_bytes, pod_network_receive_packets, pod_network_transmit_bytes, pod_network_transmit_packets] (From Ground Truth key_metrics)\\nActionable Checks:\\nCheck Trace: Search for latency anomalies in trace data, specifically check Redis operations HGET/HMSET latency\\nCheck Trace: Check trace data for frontend service calls to CartService with increased latency\\nCheck Log: Search for keyword \'http.resp.status\' and \'302\' in log files\\nCheck Metric: Check metric data for rrt and rrt_max values, specifically for redis-cart-0 service\\nCheck Metric: Monitor request and response rate metrics for services in the call chain\\nCheck Metric: Check pod_memory_working_set_bytes metric for redis-cart-0 and related pods\\nCheck Metric: Monitor network metrics for pods to detect abnormal traffic patterns",\n    "Fault Type: rrt, rrt_max, pod_network_receive_bytes, pod_network_receive_packets, pod_network_transmit_bytes, pod_network_transmit_packets\\nSymptom: Service timeouts and connection failures due to network packet corruption, leading to RedisTimeoutException and cascading failures in dependent services.\\nRoot Cause: Component [redis-cart-0] experienced severe degradation in [rrt, rrt_max] and anomalies in network metrics [pod_network_receive_bytes, pod_network_receive_packets, pod_network_transmit_bytes, pod_network_transmit_packets] indicating packet corruption. Specifically, rrt increas